                            :description """If you're looking to take your first step into a Motorsport career, we need YOU! 🏁
If you’ve ever wanted to be part of something fast-paced, inspiring, and full of future innovators, this is your moment. Whether you’re a teacher, student, motorsport fan, or simply passionate about STEM, volunteering at the National Finals is a chance to get behind the scenes of an unforgettable event. At STEM On Track, we help schools bring STEM to life through hands-on go-kart kits and online modules, giving students a real taste of engineering, motorsport, and marketing.
We’re looking for enthusiastic volunteers to help with:
⚙️ Event Marshals – keep the day running smoothly and safely
🏎️ Track & Team Support – assist teams and see innovation in action up close
🎤 Stage & Registration Helpers – welcome participants and keep the energy high
💡 All-Round STEM Champions – help wherever you’re needed and be part of the action!
Volunteering isn’t just about giving your time, it’s about making a real impact. You’ll meet like-minded people, see the next generation of STEM talent in action, and gain hands-on experience in events, teamwork, and STEM education. Plus, you’ll have a front-row seat to all the excitement on and off the track!
Join us and help power the next generation of STEM leaders. Your support makes the National Finals possible, and your enthusiasm inspires tomorrow’s engineers, innovators, and problem-solvers.
